cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper discusses a method for identifying seed words to represent named entities in a word graph, which is a common technique used in natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves building a bilingual word graph, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of community analysis to identify seed words suggests a focus on clustering and classification, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
